article.description: The Miami Heat overcame a 17-point deficit to defeat the Chicago Bulls 90-83 Monday night.
article.headline: Miami's Odom snags double-double
article.linkText: Heat overcome 17-point deficit to beat Bulls
article.story:
CHICAGO (AP) -- Brian Grant scored 12 of his 18 points in the pivotal third quarter, and the Miami Heat overcame a 17-point deficit to defeat the Chicago Bulls 90-83 Monday night. Lamar Odom had 25 points and 13 rebounds for the Heat, who have won eight of their last 12 games. Grant also had 12 rebounds, and Eddie Jones had 12 points. Jerome Williams matched his season-high with 16 rebounds to go with 14 points. But it was little consolation to the Bulls, who blew their biggest lead of the season in a stunning meltdown. Jamal Crawford, who scored 72 points in the previous two games, had a season-high 12 assists. But he finished with just eight points on 3-of-16 shooting. The rest of the Bulls weren't much better, shooting less than 40 percent. As if all that wasn't bad enough, the Bulls did it in front of Michael Jordan. Chicago is 0-3 this season when Jordan is at the game. The Bulls led by 17 points with 2:22 left in the first half before their game suddenly disintegrated into ugly mode. They didn't make a field goal for a nearly five-minute stretch that spanned halftime, and Miami took advantage with a 15-2 run. Dwyane Wade scored on a dunk worthy of his highlight reel, spinning around and slamming it in on the reverse side as the crowd oohed and aahed. He followed with a driving layup, and Rafer Alston added a 3-pointer to cut Chicago's lead to 45-33 at the half. Jones opened the second half with a three-point play, and Odom scored on a reverse and a 3 to pull Miami within 45-41. Kirk Hinrich finally interrupted the run with a 3-pointer with 9:37 left in the third, but then Grant took over. He scored his 12 points in the last 8:21 of the quarter -- matching Chicago's entire output -- and his 16-footer with 57 seconds left gave Miami a 63-62 lead, its first of the game. Odom made a short jumper to give the Heat a 77-72 lead, their largest of the game, with 4:33 to play, and they never trailed again. Kendall Gill hit a 3 to cut Miami's lead to 84-83 with 1:02 left. Odom then missed an 18-footer, and Antonio Davis snared the rebound. After a timeout, the Heat bottled up Gill along the baseline and Chicago was forced to call another timeout. But Chicago couldn't find a shot as the clock ticked down. Crawford finally took a long 3 with about 19 seconds left, but it fell way short. The Bulls were forced to foul, and Grant made a pair. The Bulls got one more chance, but Kirk Hinrich lost control of the ball under the basket and it rolled of bounds with 14 seconds left.

Game notes
Wade had to get 30 tickets for a contingent of family and friends . His parents, Jolinda and Dwyane Wade Sr., were in the cheering section, as were his brothers and sisters and his son, Zaire. ... The Bulls had a season-high 56 rebounds. ... Bulls C Eddy Curry, who missed the last seven games with a bruised knee, played 14 minutes and had 13 points and six rebounds.
